    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All thirteen credibility factors assessed or flagged; seven factors formally assessed with achieved levels documented. Monte Carlo UQ performed for primary NIH QoI and model input propagation. Velocity field and pressure-rise validation results include structured UQ links. Wall shear stress validation result (vr-04) relies on qualitative variability characterisation only — inherent variability in the reference dataset was judged insufficient to support a formal UQ node, and the hasUncertaintyQuantification link is consequently absent for that result. The assessment team accepted this gap on the basis that WSS is a secondary QoI and the primary NIH comparison carries formal UQ. Overall credibility package accepted subject to the noted aleatory uncertainty gap in vr-04.",
